weather.description: Sustained winds right around 20mph, with gusts over 30. Any rain will be gone long before kickoff, but those winds could be an issue for deeper throws and kicks.
Winds 10-15mph (and probably closer to 10), not an issue.
Low chance of a typical FL shower, no real worries here.

Models show the heaviest of the rain clearing right before kickoff, with only isolated scattered showers and a damp field left by game time. More importantly, winds are a concern, 20mph sustained winds with gusts over 30. Again problematic for deep throws and kicks, and a spot where the game flow might lean a little more heavily towards the run.
Dry, 15mph winds and some stronger gusts.

This continues to look like the windiest game of the week. Sustained winds here between 25-30mph, with gusts likely around 45. Deep passes are a no-go, intermediate passes could be a problem as well (anything not thrown on a line). The plus side here is that the winds will be somewhat parallel to the field, so maybe in one direction you can attempt some deeper throws and kicks (though I've heard from locals that winds here tend to swirl in the stadium anyways, so it's likely a mess regardless). Also a chance for some showers here, though it's not a washout. Bump down to passing, kicking, offense in general. Slight bump up to RB's and DEF.
Most of the rain clears pregame (again maybe a lingering shower or two remains, but not much). With 10-15mph winds this is looking like one of the better weather games.
10-15mph winds, dry.

I think we see winds around 25mph sustained and gusts close to 40mph early, with winds gradually winding down late (but still 15-20mph with 30mph gusts). It's also going to be very cold, temp in the 30s with a feels-like temp in the 20s. Bump down to passing/kicking/offense in general, especially in the first half. .

Lowering the impact here as I expect the worst will be gone by gametime. This is still a breezy game, with sustained winds around 15mph and gusts around 20-25, but I think it's a more manageable wind than what we'll see in CLE and BUF.
